        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 3:37AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 337 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Arrowhead State Park, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arrowhead State Park...           Quinton...
Canadian...                       Featherston...
Enterprise...                     Whitefield...
Blocker...                        Kinta...
Lewisville...                     Stigler...
Crowder...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
